ransformation in Old Industrial Regions</gtr:title><gtr:status>Closed</gtr:status><gtr:grantCategory>Fellowship</gtr:grantCategory><gtr:grantReference>ES/G026726/1</gtr:grantReference><gtr:abstractText>&lt;p>The fellowship aims to develop issues arising out of the author's PhD research on coalfield regeneration trajectories.&lt;/p>

&lt;p>The PhD focus on Leicestershire and Kent specifically addressed the tensions arising out of places being at the centre and the margins of national and local political agendas. &lt;/p>

&lt;p>The main objective of the fellowship is the strategic dissemination of data and results, and discussions with policy-makers and communities.&lt;/p>

&lt;p>The research highlighted issues of exclusion through discourses and mechanisms of participation. Dissemination therefore aims to improve the communication process and adjust the expectations of all &amp;quot;regeneration stake holders&amp;quot;.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>

&lt;p>The PhD research is an examination of the specificity of place and the meaning of locality in the process of restructuring. &lt;/p>

&lt;p>Transformation or its failure emerged as a result of strategies of adaptation, resistance, imposition and co-operation. Of utmost importance is the way local priorities are brought onto the national agenda and vice versa. The result is that place matters and it needs more attention.&lt;/p>

&lt;p>Close collaboration with the Welsh Institute of Social and Economic Research Data and Methods at Cardiff will enable the development of a mixed methods approach. This will lead to a more nuanced view of what is termed successful regeneration.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br />&lt;/p></gtr:abstractText><gtr:fund><gtr:end>2010-05-31</gtr:end><gtr:funder url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/organisation/924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE"><gtr:id>924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE</gtr:id><gtr:name>ESRC</gtr:name></gtr:funder><gtr:start>2009-06-01</gtr:start><gtr:type>INCOME_ACTUAL</gtr:type><gtr:valuePounds>68716</gtr:valuePounds></gtr:fund><gtr:output><gtr:artisticAndCreativeProductOutputs/><gtr:collaborationOutputs/><gtr:disseminationOutputs/><gtr:exploitationOutputs/><gtr:furtherFundingOutputs/><gtr:impactSummaryOutputs/><gtr:intellectualPropertyOutputs/><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs/><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications/><gtr:identifiers><gtr:identifier type="RCUK">ES/G026726/1</gtr:identifier></gtr:identifiers><gtr:healthCategories/><gtr:researchActivities/><gtr:researchSubjects><gtr:researchSubject><gtr:id>B57EEFB7-602E-4F5D-92E4-A0C265266249</gtr:id><gtr:percentage>0</gtr:percentage><gtr:text>Demography &amp; human geography</gtr:text></gtr:researchSubject><gtr:researchSubject><gtr:id>5D762B83-597E-4E91-B2F7-04CBB955175C</gtr:id><gtr:percentage>0</gtr:percentage><gtr:text>Pol. sci. &amp; internat. studies</gtr:text></gtr:researchSubject><gtr:researchSubject><gtr:id>F0322ED6-113F-4530-BA5E-562216587E68</gtr:id><gtr:percentage>0</gtr:percentage><gtr:text>Sociology</gtr:text></gtr:researchSubject></gtr:researchSubjects><gtr:researchTopics><gtr:researchTopic><gtr:id>3A4CB57C-9B22-41A2-AB15-127503299365</gtr:id><gtr:percentage>0</gtr:percentage><gtr:text>Human Geography</gtr:text></gtr:researchTopic><gtr:research